# WebAuthn/Passkeys in Embedded Browser

## Goal
Support passkeys (1Password, Touch ID, iCloud Keychain) in the app's browser panels.

## Findings

### `<webview>` (current) does not support WebAuthn
- `navigator.credentials.create()` / `.get()` silently fails
- WebAuthn does NOT go through Electron's permission handlers (`setPermissionRequestHandler`, `setPermissionCheckHandler`) — nothing logs
- Adding `publickey-credentials-create` / `publickey-credentials-get` to allowed permissions has no effect
- This is a known Electron limitation — `<webview>` is soft-deprecated and doesn't wire up the OS authenticator

### Options explored

| Option | Viable? | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| Expand permission handler | No | WebAuthn bypasses permission system entirely in webview |
| Desktop handoff (open in system browser) | No | Session/cookies don't transfer back to webview — user stays logged out |
| Migrate to `BrowserWindow` | Technically yes | Supports WebAuthn via OS credential provider, but can't embed in DOM — must manually sync window bounds to React layout. Painful for multi-device grid |
| `BrowserView` | No | Deprecated since Electron 30 |
| Inject 1Password content scripts | No | Fragile, breaks on updates, likely violates TOS |

### `BrowserWindow` vs `<webview>` tradeoffs
- BrowserWindow: WebAuthn works, first-class Electron support, but no DOM embedding — need manual bound syncing, z-order management, especially bad for multi-device grid
- webview: trivial React integration, but no WebAuthn, soft-deprecated

## Status
**Blocked** — no clean solution exists today. Revisit when:
- Electron adds WebAuthn support to `<webview>` (unlikely given deprecation)
- Electron ships a new embeddable web content primitive
- A community solution emerges for BrowserWindow ↔ React layout sync
